CLIHTTP headerGo SDK <pre><code>memory --project-token emt_abc123... agents list
# or via environment variable:
export MEMORY_PROJECT_TOKEN=emt_abc123...
memory agents list
</code></pre> <pre><code>Authorization: Bearer emt_abc123...
</code></pre> <pre><code>client, err := sdk.New(sdk.Config{
    ServerURL: "https://api.dev.emergent-company.ai",
    Auth: sdk.AuthConfig{
        Mode:   "apitoken",
        APIKey: "emt_abc123...",
    },
})
</code></pre>

API (streaming — recommended)API (non-streaming) <p>Returns a server-sent event (SSE) stream with partial tokens as they are generated:</p> <pre><code>POST /api/chat/stream
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "conversationId": "&lt;uuid&gt;",
  "message": "What decisions did we make about the database?"
}
</code></pre> <p>SSE events: <pre><code>data: {"type":"token","content":"We decided "}
data: {"type":"token","content":"to use PostgreSQL "}
data: {"type":"citations","citations":[{"objectId":"...","title":"Use PostgreSQL"}]}
data: {"type":"done"}
</code></pre></p> <pre><code>POST /api/chat/{conversationId}/messages
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "role": "user",
  "content": "What decisions did we make about the database?"
}
</code></pre>

CLIAPI <pre><code>memory documents delete &lt;doc-id&gt; --project my-project
</code></pre> <pre><code>DELETE /api/documents/{id}
</code></pre> <p>Bulk delete: <pre><code>DELETE /api/documents
{ "ids": ["doc_1", "doc_2"] }
</code></pre></p> <p>Warning</p> <p>Deleting a document removes its chunks and embeddings. Graph objects extracted from it are not automatically deleted — they remain in the graph.</p>
